title: For Sale:  1895 Loewe Mauser
postcontent:
Hey there. Up for sale is my 1895 Chilean Loewe Berlin Mauser in 7x57 (7mm Mauser) for $300 OBRO. The gun is in perfect working condition with ALL matching serial numbers. I have owned the gun for 10 years and only ever put 4 rounds through it to test it using Federal ammo. The gun is VERY clean with no pitting, rust, warps, cracks, or breaks. The bore is very shiny and kept oiled.

The gun has been taken completely apart by my qualified and professional gunsmith. He went through it, cleaned it in detail, greased the contact points on the trigger/sear, oiled the necessary spots with CLP, cleaned the action, cleaned the magazine box, cleaned up the barrel, and spent two hours carefully wiping down and cleaning the stock. This was after I obtained it, cleaned it myself, and shot it. The gun has always been stored in my Liberty safe in my temperature controlled house. It is as original as they come and VERY clean for its age. This thing has been gone through meticulously and doesn't have an ounce of dirt/cosmoline/gunk in it. Even the inside of the bolt is spotless. All in all it has always been well loved and has the original cleaning rod.

I am asking $300 OBRO. After months of watching them on here and GunBroker it would appear that in this condition the average sale price is $350 - $400, sometimes going as high as $450. It kills me to sell this thing but being that its my only 7mm Mauser I can't say I have an interest in buying ammo for it and my safe is almost completely full. Its been a safe queen for years and only ever removed to be cleaned. If you're a Mauser guy, this one is for you.

title: Want To Buy:  Colt 1911 commander, officers, or government
postcontent:
I'm looking for a project 1911 Colt pistol.  Condition is not as important as structural integrity; it can look like crap but as long as it hasn't had reconstructive surgery or major damage, it will probably be OK. 

I'd prefer an officers or commander but anything will work.  Also prefer stainless but blue is OK as long as it's all steel; no alloy frames.  Missing parts are OK as long as you have frame, slide, and barrel.  If the barrel is shot out, I may still be interested.  So if you've got a beater, send me a picture and your asking price.  

Due to the loads of stupid offers I've received in response to this ad, I'd like to make a few things crystal clear:
- this is not your opportunity to display your self perceived gun trading wizardry by trying to pass your junked up 1911 clone that you "melted" with a Dremel and used JB Weld to get the sights on on to me as "customized" or "super rare."
- I will pay wholesale or better depending on condition.  If you have a "Frankengun" I will pay what it's worth to me.  But...if you've shopped your gun around to various dealers and were told it's worth considerably less than you had hoped, I'm probably going to tell you the same thing.
- I'm pretty sure I'm not stupid and just because you put a Wilson (or any other brand), part on your gun doesn't make it custom.
- I will not cheat you.  Please show me the same respect.
